narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: great course, take it. if you are NOT a mechanical engineer and enjoy the product design process, take it. this means designing and fabricating a working prototype, it may be time consuming, but absolutely worth it if you are an engineering student in any discipline.
I would take this class if you are an ME senior regardless of ABET or not. It is really fun and rewarding, that said it is a lot of work, and time.
Yes, amazing class, first chance to build something.

This course is excellent for exposure to a team setting in which everyone must work together to ensure a successful outcome. It mimics the real world in several ways. You will learn a lot about interfacing with a team to achieve time sensitive objectives. You will be exposed to eEvery part of the design and development process - Idea Development, CAD design, Team Decisions, and Fabrication. Definitely take this course if you plan on getting involved with industrial design and development.
You get to come up with a project and then you actually make it! Definitely recommend it. This IS the reason why you picked mechanical engineering as your major.
Amazing course, teaches you how to solve a real life design problem as well as practical engineering skills, should be taken.
Great, hands-on class for MechE majors. Very fun, and highly recommended if you like hands-on design classes.
